title: New Mexico High School Football Rankings
text:
New Mexico High School Football Rankings Kyle Henderson NMPreps.com Publisher 
Each Monday on NMPreps.com we rank the Top 25 teams in New Mexico regardless of Class as well as Class by Class rankings. Sign Up For A Premium Subscription Now - Just 33 cents a day! In Case You Missed It Saturday Scores Friday Scoreboard Here Breaking Down The October 5th Top 25 Rankings 
Cleveland now 6-0 remains the No. 1 overall ranked team in New Mexico after defeating previously unbeaten Eldorado 41-34 last Friday Night. The Storm are open in week 7. The Alamogordo Tigers continue to roll through their schedule un-touched still at 6-0 after beaitng Deming 56-12. 
The Tigers travel to Artesia to take on the Bulldogs in week 7. No. 3 is the Eldorado Eagles who moved up two spots after hanging tough with Cleveland 41-34, the Eagles jump into district play taking on La Cueva Friday. 
The Centennial Hawks are 5-0 heading into district play this weekend against Los Lunas, the Hawks were open in week 6. At the No. 5 spot is Las Cruces who defeated Artesia 41-25, the Bulldawgs now 4-2 this year will head to Deming to take on the Wildcats. Continue Reading Here NMPreps.com's October 5th Top 5
